Animal's Super Senses - Episode 4: Taste & Smell | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'Animal's Super Senses - Episode 5' here: https://youtu.be/S4znYd2EZ3c

In this episode of Animal Super Senses, we examine how things taste, and how vital scent is from the animal perspective. But their sense of smell will also detect the scent of odorants carried through the air. In mammals, taste receptor cells are scattered over the tongue. In other creatures, they can be located in some fairly odd places. How taste and smell receptors work underwater, well, it's a whole other world.
